code:

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.boxplot(x="region", y="income", data=data, palette="Set3")
    ax.set(xlabel='Region', ylabel='Income')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of income across different regions?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.scatterplot(x="pct", y="income", data=data, hue="region", palette="Set2")
    plt.title("What is the relationship between income and percentage of population in a region?", wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='income', hue='group', multiple='stack', kde=False)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of income across different income groups?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Income')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.legend(title='Income Group')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
